/**
  $(ProjectName) : PlayState 
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------
  A game state.

  One of the basic states for this project, together with MenuState. This 
  represents the game (gameplay) state.

  HaxeFlixel uses isolated states to avoid problems like memory leaks (well, 
  according to what the manual says).

  @author     $(DefaultUser) 
  @since      $(ProjectName) 0.0.1
  @version    0.0.1
**/
class PlayState extends FlxState 
{
  /**
    State constructor.

    Called when this class is loaded.
  **/
  override public function create():Void 
  {
    // Calling "parent" create
    super.create();
  }
      
  /**
    State update method.

    Called every frame, it's responsible for updating the state of every 
    event and object in this state.

    @param elapsed Float 
        Time, in seconds, since the last frame
  **/
  override public function update( elapsed:Float ):Void 
  {
    // Calling "parent" update
    super.update( elapsed );
  }
}
